('Fernstrum, Wendy', 'Literary essences', '-', 'by Wendy A. Fernstrum', '-', 'Minneapolis', 'Fernwerks', '2005', 'Handmade clamshell box covered with Japanese bookbinding fabric. Includes a set of 26 essence vials, 26 diagnostic cards, a hand-bound guidebook for using the essences, a set of index cards, and a pair of tweezers|Booklet entitled Using literary essences|One of twenty-five signed copies', 'According to the artist, this is a step by step guide to the use of literary essences as natural health remedies for emotional and spiritual well-being. Each vial contains lozenge-sized circles allegedly punched from pages of twenty-six works of literature, in a solution that captures the precise and particular odor of that work. Each essence - hence, each book - cures, alleviates, or engages certain feelings, symptoms, or conditions. The index cards indicate which. Directions call for the ingestion of four paper circles to commence healing', '-', '-', '-', '-', '-', '-', '-', 'Artists'' books|Health', 'Minnesota', '-', '-', '-', '-', '-', '-', '-', '-', '1 box', '061110s2005    mnual         000 0 eng d', 'specol_N7433_4_F47_L58_2005');
