ed some trucks for Circus Vargas when they were in Southern California.  Percy Turner kept hoping to find someone else who could provide the financial means to allow him to take out another circus, but his failing health and increased costs prevented him from ever touring again. The Turner Bros. Circus officially closed for good on July 4, 1959.  Ralph Rodgers, whose "day job" was as a gas service man for San Diego Gas & Electric, was an avid circus model builder and lifelong circus devotee.   He spent his lifetime learning about the circus, following all the circuses--figuratively and later literally-- and becoming friends with many of the well-known circus performers and clowns of the day, many of whom were also model-builders.   Ralph Rodgers'' wife, Mary Ann, was supportive of her husband''s hobby and also worked with him and attended conventions with him.  They had four sons:  Patrick, Kevin, Michael, and John, all of whom had model circuses named after them.  The circuses were created in the Rodgers'' backyard in El Cajon and reflected Ralph''s desire to preserve the form and spirit of the circus during its heyday of the 1920s and 30s.  Images of Rodgers'' circus can be viewed online at: http://dreamingincircus.com/media/rr-circus/rr-circus.htm', '-', '-', '-', '-', 'Turner, Percy|Rodgers, Ralph|Evans, Merle|Hayden, Robert|Jacobs, Lou|Kreischer, Lou|MacDougall, Robert S|Parker, Jim|Posey, Jake|Strong, John|Wallenda, Karl', 'Big Apple Circus|Circus Model Builders International|Circus World Museum (Baraboo, Wis|Cole Bros. Circus|Clyde Beatty-Cole Bros. Circus|Hagenbeck-Wallace Circus|Ringling Brothers Barnum and Bailey Combined Shows|Sells-Floto Circus|Wenatchee Youth Circus', 'African American business enterprises|Amusements|Circus wagons|Circus|Circus|Circus|Circus|Clowns|Popular culture', 'California|California|California|California|California|Florida|California, Southern', 'Archival resources|History|Archival resources|Archival resources|Archival resources|Archival resources|Archival resources|Archival resources|History', '20th century|20th century|20th century|20th century|20th century', 'La Jolla (San Diego, Calif', 'History', '-', 'Audiotapes|Clippings|Correspondence|Costumes (character dress|Drawings|Ephemera|Magazines (periodicals|Phonograph records|Photographs|Postcards|Posters|Slides (photographs|Videotapes', 'Turner, Percy', '-', '76', '130114i19301990cau           000 0 eng d', 'specol_0388_box57_folder3_ov7');
