('Klinger, Walter A', 'Walter A. Klinger papers', '-', '-', 'Dog tags', '-', '-', '-', '-', 'The Walter A. Klinger (1912-2003) papers consists of photographs, correspondence, clippings, and typescripts that document the pre-war Austrian lives of Walter, his wife Hertha, and father Adolf; their emigration via Trinidad in the early 1940s; and from their lives in the United States. Walter A. Klinger was born May 12, 1912 in Vienna, Austria. In 1929, he began working for Warner Bros. in Vienna, and subsequently spent his entire career working in some aspect of the film industry. He and his family emigrated to the United States in 1940, settling in Los Angeles.  He died on March 15, 2003 in Camarillo, California', '-', '-', '-', '-', '-', 'Klinger, Walter A|Klinger, Hertha Bley', 'Warner Bros. Pictures (1923-1967', 'Immigrants|Immigrants|Motion pictures, American|Motion pictures and globalization|Motion pictures|Motion pictures|Motion pictures|World War, 1939-1945', 'America|Trinidad and Tobago|Germany|Argentina|Argentina|Germany|United States', 'History|History|History|Archival resources', '20th century|20th century', 'Germany|United States', 'Emigration and immigration|Armed Forces', '-', 'Clippings|Correspondence|Legal documents|Typescripts', 'Klinger, Hertha Bley', '-', '6.67', '150408i16262002cau           000 0 eng d', 'specol_6044_box7_envelope4');
